.TH "pci_epc_write_header" 9 "pci_epc_write_header" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_epc_write_header \- write standard configuration header
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_epc_write_header
.BI "(struct pci_epc *epc "  ","
.BI "u8 func_no "  ","
.BI "struct pci_epf_header *header "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "epc" 12
the EPC device to which the configuration header should be written
.IP "func_no" 12
the endpoint function number in the EPC device
.IP "header" 12
standard configuration header fields
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoke to write the configuration header to the endpoint controller. Every
endpoint controller will have a dedicated location to which the standard
configuration header would be written. The callback function should write
the header fields to this dedicated location.
